<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">If you think you are alone in wondering h=
ow many tablespoons in an ounce, you are not.  In every home cook=E2=80=99s=
 life, there comes a time when this question pops up.</p>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">Tablespoons are the go-to for many, but w=
hat happens when ounces are in a recipe?  Or visa versa.  No matter the cir=
cumstance, converting tablespoons to ounces is a simple calculation.</p>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">Here is a comprehensive guide to help you=
 convert from tablespoons to ounces.</p>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">No matter where the recipe is from, with =
this helpful information, you will be able to calculate the number of ounce=
s or tablespoons needed.</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_1_tablet" class=3D"=
adthrive-ad adthrive-sticky-container adthrive-content adthrive-content-1 a=
dthrive-ad-cls"></div>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">While ounces may be commonplace for cooks=
 in the United States, they are not used in Europe and other parts of the w=
orld. Conversion in recipes for cooks in parts of Europe, Australia, and Af=
rica is typical.</p>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">Check out this post about <strong><a href=
=3D"https://www.100daysofrealfood.com/how-many-pints-in-a-gallon/">How Many=
 Pints in a Gallon</a></strong> and <strong><a href=3D"https://www.100dayso=
frealfood.com/how-many-grams-in-an-ounce-with-conversion-chart/">How Many G=
rams in an Ounce</a></strong>.</p>



