<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-what-is-a-tablespoon">What is a Tabl=
espoon?</h2>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">A tablespoon is probably the simplest of =
all measuring tools.  The tablespoon is typically used as a measurement too=
l in both baking and cooking.  It is by no means the most accurate tool, bu=
t it is convenient and beloved by many cooks.&nbsp;</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_=
Content_3_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-sticky-container adthrive-c=
ontent adthrive-content-3 adthrive-ad-cls"></div>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">A tablespoon is also equal:</p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li class=3D"has-medium-font-size">3 teaspoons</li>



<li class=3D"has-medium-font-size">14.8 ml in the US via the Imperial syste=
m</li>



<li class=3D"has-medium-font-size">15ml via the metric system</li>



<li class=3D"has-medium-font-size">20ml in Australia</li>
</ul>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">A tablespoon is also used as a piece of c=
utlery at the table.  In medieval times, people would carry their spoons ar=
ound to eat with.  They would have their own personal spoon!  Later on, fla=
tware was introduced.  This detail is most relevant to European countries.&=
nbsp; Tablespoons are now used every day by cooks and bakers.&nbsp; They ar=
e part of every measuring spoon set.</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_4_table=
t" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-sticky-container adthrive-content adthrive=
-content-4 adthrive-ad-cls"></div>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">Learn more about <strong><a href=3D"https=
://www.100daysofrealfood.com/how-many-tablespoons-in-1-4-cup/">How Many Tab=
lespoons are in =C2=BC Cup</a></strong> too!</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-what-is-an-ounce">What is an Ounce?<=
/h2>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">An ounce is typically found in recipes fr=
om the United States and Britain.  One pound is equal to 16 ounces.</p>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">You will find ounces abbreviated as =E2=
=80=9Coz.=E2=80=9D  Fluid ounces are different from dry ounces and are abbr=
eviated Fl oz.</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_5_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-a=
d adthrive-sticky-container adthrive-content adthrive-content-5 adthrive-ad=
-cls"></div>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-how-to-convert-from-tablespoons-to-o=
unces">How to Convert From Tablespoons to Ounces</h2>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">Ready to get cooking or baking?  Need to =
convert from tablespoons to ounces?  Easy!  If you are trying to work out h=
ow many tablespoons in an ounce, consider the following:</p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li class=3D"has-medium-font-size">There are 2 tablespoons in an ounce.</li=
>



<li class=3D"has-medium-font-size">2 ounces equal 4 tablespoons.</li>



<li class=3D"has-medium-font-size">4 ounces equals 8 tablespoons</li>



<li class=3D"has-medium-font-size">6 ounces equals 12 tablespoons</li>



<li class=3D"has-medium-font-size">8 ounces equals 16 tablespoons</li>



<li class=3D"has-medium-font-size">10 ounces equals 20 tablespoons</li>
</ul><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_6_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-st=
icky-container adthrive-content adthrive-content-6 adthrive-ad-cls"></div>



