<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Tips for Measuring Liquid Ingredients</h2>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">Examples of wet ingredients are oil, milk=
, and water. Measuring liquid ingredients in tablespoons is super easy. It =
is not, however, the most accurate way of measuring. Unless your recipe is =
very precise, go ahead and use a tablespoon, though.</p>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">Make sure the tablespoon is sitting on a =
level surface.  If the spoon does not balance on a surface, hold it straigh=
t in front of you. Pour the liquid into the spoon and bend down to meet the=
 surface eye level.  The liquid should reach just under the surface of the =
spoon.</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_8_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthri=
ve-sticky-container adthrive-content adthrive-content-8 adthrive-ad-cls"></=
div>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">Measuring fluid ounces can be done on a s=
cale (with fluid ounce measurements) or on a weighted scale.</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Tips for Measuring Dry Ingredients</h2>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">Examples of dry ingredients are flour, su=
gar, and spices.  Dry ingredients are commonly measured in cups, grams, or =
dry ounces.</p>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">If you want to find out how many tablespo=
ons are in an ounce, the answer is 2.</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_9_tabl=
et" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-sticky-container adthrive-content adthriv=
e-content-9 adthrive-ad-cls"></div>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">Use a scale to measure dry ounces accurat=
ely.  Alternatively, use a spoon or cup, depending on the amount of dry ing=
redients.</p>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size">To measure dry ingredients in a tablespoo=
n, ensure the flour or sugar is loose and light. It should be aerated.  Fil=
l the spoon with the dry ingredient and level off the top of the ingredient=
.  Use the back of a spoon to do this.</p>



